The paper deals with source code obfuscation, which is a common technique used in computer security to protect software from reverse engineering and unauthorized access. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and text-based applications. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
